data.title: Rosemount High School
data.text:
Students on the "A" Honor Roll earned a GPA (Grade Point Average) of 3.666 or higher during this trimester. Grades from only this trimester were used in the GPA calculation. GPA is calculated with the following numerical values: A = 4.0, A- = 3.7, B+ = 3.3, B = 3.0, B- = 2.7, C+ = 2.3, C = 2.0, C- = 1.7, D+ = 1.3, D = 1.0, D- = .7, E - .3, F = 0. To be eligible for Honor Roll recognition, freshmen and sophomores must meet the registration minimums of six credits per trimester and a junior and senior must meet the registration minimums of five credits per trimester.

Students on the "B" Honor Roll earned a GPA (Grade Point Average) of 3.000 or higher during this trimester. Grades from only this trimester were used in the GPA calculation. GPA is calculated with the following numerical values: A = 4.0, A- = 3.7, B+ = 3.3, B = 3.0, B- = 2.7, C+ = 2.3, C = 2.0, C- = 1.7, D+ = 1.3, D = 1.0, D- = .7, E - .3, F = 0. To be eligible for Honor Roll recognition, freshmen and sophomores must meet the registration minimums of six credits per trimester and a junior and senior must meet the registration minimums of five credits per trimester.
